/* ============================================================
   FRESH24 DESIGN SYSTEM v1
   ------------------------------------------------------------
   Source of truth: Fresh24 Brand Family board. Shared across
   Fresh24 Fellowship, Fresh Launch Studio, Fresh24 Cares, and
   Fresh24 Collective. Any future Fresh24 product should inherit
   these tokens rather than hardcoding new values.

   BRAND PHILOSOPHY
   Warm, hopeful, peaceful, premium, editorial, minimal, purposeful,
   human, welcoming, timeless. Never: tech-startup, church-software,
   corporate, busy, flashy, or AI-generated-looking. When in doubt
   between adding a visual element or adding breathing room, choose
   breathing room. Litmus test for any UI decision: "Would this look
   like it belongs beside the brand board?"

   COLOR TOKENS (see COLORS object below)
   Cream #F3EFE6 — primary background
   Sand  #D9C8B3 — secondary neutral, soft card/badge fills
   Olive #4B5B45 — primary dark (replaces earlier Midnight Green;
                   softer and less saturated per brand direction)
   Charcoal #1C1C1C — body text, near-black accents
   Clay  #A47F63 — warm accent (replaces earlier Warm Gold — brand
                   board explicitly calls for avoiding bright gold)
   All other token names (goldSoft, sage, peach, lavender, etc.) are
   kept for backward compatibility with existing component code, but
   their VALUES now resolve to tints/shades of the five colors above
   — nothing outside this official palette is introduced.

   TYPOGRAPHY TOKENS (see FONTS object below)
   Heading: Fraunces (closest available open-source match to Canela's
   warm, editorial, slightly irregular old-style serif character —
   Canela itself is a paid foundry font not available via Google
   Fonts or open CDNs).
   Body: Manrope (specified directly in the brand board; available
   as an open font, used as-is).
   No script or decorative fonts. Italic serif accents are fine and
   used deliberately for quote-like emphasis.

   SPACING APPROACH
   Generous, breathing-room-first. Section padding stays large;
   prefer fewer, calmer elements over dense arrangements.

   RADIUS / CARD APPROACH
   Soft, consistently rounded corners (RADIUS token below). Cards use
   very soft, low-opacity shadows — never heavy or high-contrast.

   BUTTON RULES
   Pill-shaped (999px radius), one primary (Olive), one accent (Clay),
   one outline. No harsh drop shadows; shadow tokens use low opacity
   tinted from Olive/Clay rather than pure black.

   FORM RULES
   Inputs use soft Sand-toned borders on a Cream field background,
   generous padding, rounded corners matching the card language.

   ICON RULES
   Simple, single-tone line/emoji icons kept small and restrained;
   avoid multi-color icon sets or illustration-heavy graphics. (Note:
   current build still uses emoji for a few UI icons as a pragmatic,
   low-risk choice — a fully custom line-icon set is a reasonable
   future refinement, not done in this pass to keep the diff small.)

   PHOTOGRAPHY DIRECTION
   Natural light, warm tones, real unposed moments — coffee shops,
   homes, parks, real conversation and community. Avoid dramatic HDR
   or stock-photo staging.

   MOTION / ANIMATION RESTRAINT
   Subtle only: gentle tap-scale (0.98) and soft transitions (~160ms).
   No bouncing, no flashy entrance animations, respects
   prefers-reduced-motion.

   ACCESSIBILITY CONSIDERATIONS
   Body text (Charcoal on Cream/White) maintains strong contrast.
   Clay-on-Cream and Olive-on-Cream both checked for readable contrast
   at body text sizes. Focus states remain visible (gold/clay outline
   on interactive elements). Reduced-motion preference respected.
   ============================================================ */

